hs_Para.QuestionText:
To ask the Secretary of
State for Communities and Local Government (1) how many Article 4
directions were put in place by local authorities in 2012;

(2)
what estimate he has made of the cost to a local authority of putting
in place an Article 4 direction;

To ask the Secretary of State for
Education (1) what guidance he has provided to local authorities on the
delivery of youth services;

(2)
what steps he is taking to promote (a) local accountability and
(b) collaboration in the delivery of youth services;

(5)
what minimum expectations of delivery he has issued to local
authorities on the delivery of youth services;

To ask the Secretary of State for
Health (1) what involvement Sir David Nicholson had in (a)
commissioning and (b) producing the NHS Next Stage Review;

To ask the Secretary of State for
Justice (1) what the cost was of legal aid in North Wales in each of
the last five years;

(2)
how many legal firms have participated in the legal aid system in each
of the last five years;

(4)
what the highest day rate paid for external legal advice by his
Department was since 7 May 2010;

(2)
whether the funding announced in the 2013 Spending Round to improve air
links to London will be used to restore links that no longer operate;

(3)
what proportion of matched funding must be provided as a condition of
accessing the funding announced to improve air links to London;

To ask the
Secretary of State for Transport (1) if he will instruct High Speed 2
Ltd to carry out a feasibility study of Option 8 at Euston station;

(2)
what legislative proposals the Government plans to bring forward to
tackle alcohol duty fraud;

To ask the Secretary of State for
Work and Pensions how many Atos assessment centres there are in the UK;
and how many have disabled parking facilities.
